<|startoftext|>Our favorite brunch spot! We love how the menu offers a variety of tapas (3 for $5), and the atmosphere is inviting and cozy. Great cocktails and great service. We have always been very pleased with the food and service here at The Cafe at the Cosmopolitan. Our favorite dishes: fried wings (better than those at Planet Hollywood in Tempe), sashimi appetizer (freshly prepared), and the chef rotates the skewers before your eyes. Consistently delicious and a great combination of dishes, it's worth the trip to Las Vegas. Go-to for great tapas for the whole family :)<|endoftext|>
