<|startoftext|>A good number of places are around town to get pizza. I've never had better than this. The crust is thin and sweet, like Cracker Barrel. The crust has great smoke flavor and a little smokey acid. You can tell it's not cheap. I would recommend your friends and family to give them a try. My boyfriend got the Greek pizza and he said it was one of the best he had had in a long time. His daughter had the ham. She wasn't as impressed with the pizza like my son. We both agreed the cheese on the crust was toasted. It's hard to mess up when the cheese is not even the least bit intentional. \n\nPricing is great. There's a nice layout of the menu items. In addition to that the staff is not pushy. The only minor quibble I had about this place was that a guy working the front counter would stop by at least three times a day to have a conversation with us, but no longer, since we were no longer working.\n\nAtmosphere is good and you'll find yourself coming here often. However, I've never been so disappointed in my life with a pizza place as I did with this. The customer service and the food was both lacking. There was no remorse or apologize being or a desire for either us or our company to make things right. What more do you want? Honestly, I can't wait till my next experience!<|endoftext|>
